Bring a large #pot{} of @salt{} water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Pick @parsley{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems; roughly chop leaves. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

Once water is boiling, add @penne pasta{6%ounce} to #pot{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add @prosciutto{2%ounce} slices in a single layer; sear until browned and crispy, ~{2-3%minutes} per side.

> TIP: If the prosciutto starts to crisp too quickly, reduce heat to medium.

Turn off heat; transfer prosciutto to a #paper towel-lined plate{}. Reserve oil in pan (you'll use it to cook the chicken in the next step).

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and half the @fry seasoning{1%tablespoon}.

Heat pan with reserved oil over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

> TIP: Add an additional drizzle of oil if needed.

Turn off heat; transfer chicken to a #cutting board{} to rest. Wipe out pan.

Heat @butter{2%tablespoon} in pan used for chicken over medium-high heat.

Add garlic; cook, stirring occasionally, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add @cream sauce base{4%ounce}, @cream cheese{2%tablespoon}, a big pinch of @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

Add drained penne and @peas{4%ounce}. Cook, stirring, until peas are warmed through and sauce has slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

> TIP: If needed, stir in reserved pasta cooking water a splash at a time until pasta is coated in a creamy sauce.

Stir in half the parsley, a big squeeze of lemon juice, and a pinch of @?chili flakes{1%teaspoon} if desired.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide pasta between bowls. Top with chicken. Crumble prosciutto over top.

> TIP: Or crumble half the prosciutto and top the pasta with the remaining larger pieces.

Sprinkle with lemon zest, @parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}, remaining parsley, and a pinch of chili flakes to taste. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.